The X coordinate, is this
distance right over here,

00:07:06.814 --> 00:07:08.821
which is once again going to be X,

00:07:08.821 --> 00:07:11.879
which is square root of two over two.

00:07:11.879 --> 00:07:18.220
Now, what is the tangent of
pi over four going to be?

00:07:18.220 --> 00:07:21.074
Well the tangent of pi over
four is sine of pi over four

00:07:21.074 --> 00:07:25.346
over cosine of pi over four.

00:07:25.346 --> 00:07:27.714
Now both of these are
the exact same thing.

00:07:27.714 --> 00:07:28.947
They're both square root of two over two.

00:07:28.947 --> 00:07:30.258
So you're going to have
square root of two over two,

00:07:30.258 --> 00:07:34.273
divided by two over two, well
that's just going to give you one.

00:07:34.273 --> 00:07:35.994
And that also makes
since, because remember

00:07:35.994 --> 00:07:39.411
the tangent of this angle
is the slope of this line.

00:07:39.411 --> 00:07:41.822
And we see the slope,
for every X we move in

00:07:41.822 --> 00:07:44.575
the horizontal direction we move X up.

00:07:44.575 --> 00:07:48.247
So our change in Y over
change in X is essentially

00:07:48.247 --> 00:07:51.927
X over X, which is equal to one.

